						<summary>

						<p>Slab lying about a furlong to the south-west of the Saṇgamēśvara svāmi temple.</p>						

						<p>16th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>This undated inscription can be assigned to the 16th century on the basis of palaeography.</p>						

						<p>Records the gift of lands at the rate of 50 <hi rend="italic">varāhas</hi> to certain Timmapa with a stipulation to play the <hi rend="italic">Vīṇa</hi> and the <hi rend="italic">Kinnara</hi> instruments in the temple of Sangamēśvara at Pālem by him and his descendants.</p>						

						</summary>
